    "For Hausknecht and Stone (2015), mapping states to actions based only on the four previous game states (stacking the frames in a pre-processing step) prevents the DQN agent from achieving the best performance in games that require remembering faraway events from a large number of frames, because in those games the future states and rewards depend on several previous states."
